  "commentary": "With SPX at 6829.85 sitting just below the massive +125.96B gamma wall at 6830, dealers are aggressively selling into this rally to hedge their long gamma position, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime confirms dealers will fade moves away from equilibrium, and with the spot trading within the dense positive gamma zone (6820-6850 strikes all showing significant stabilizing flow), expect strong mean reversion pressure back toward the 6825-6830 cluster. Watch for continued selling pressure if we break above 6830, but the wall_break event suggests we're already seeing rejection from these levels with dealers stepping in as natural sellers.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pushed back down toward 6825 as dealers sell the rally.",
